color Property
Purpose:
The color property is used to set the text color of an element.
color: value;
##color = Text Color

# CSS Color Properties

| Property | One-Line Definition |
|-----------|---------------------|
| `color` | Sets the color of the text content. |
| `background-color` | Sets the background color of an element. |
| `border-color` | Sets the color of all four borders. |
| `border-top-color` | Sets the color of the top border. |
| `border-right-color` | Sets the color of the right border. |
| `border-bottom-color` | Sets the color of the bottom border. |
| `border-left-color` | Sets the color of the left border. |
| `outline-color` | Sets the color of the outline outside the border. |
| `text-decoration-color` | Sets the color of text decorations such as underline or strike-through. |
| `caret-color` | Sets the color of the blinking text cursor in input fields. |
| `accent-color` | Sets the color of form controls like checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders. |

## Most Commonly Used

- `color` → Text color
- `background-color` → Background color
- `border-color` → Border color
- `text-decoration-color` → Underline/line-through color
- `caret-color` → Input cursor color
- `accent-color` → Checkbox, radio button, slider color
